It can be problematic when multiple predictors have a high degree of correlation with one another, commonly called _multicollinearity_^[Meaning that multiple predictors are “co-linear” or have a strong linear relationship with one another] and is a fairly frequent occurrence in many data sets. For example, recall the visualization of the correlation matrix in @fig-corr-plot. The heatmap shows that there are a number of climate-related predictors that have high degrees of correlation with one another.




